{{Sandbox|Please, do not remove this line. Thank you.}}
{{Infobox Single | name = My Bologna | Cover = My_Bologna.jpg | Caption = [[Singles (info)|Single]] by [["Weird Al" Yankovic]] | Released = December 25, 1979 | Recorded = September 1979 | Genre = Comedy | Format = 7" | B-side = [[School Cafeteria]] | Album = {{Al|"Weird Al" Yankovic}} | Length = 4:32 | Language = English | Label = Capitol Records | Producer = [["Weird Al" Yankovic]] | Last single = | Next single = {{Sg|Another One Rides The Bus}} }}
My Bologna is a parody of Knack's My Sharona by Weird Al. Dr. Demento recieved the song from Yankovic and aired it on The Dr. Demento Show. It placed a number one spot on Dr. Demento's Funny Five countdown. It was released on [[Album:"Weird Al" Yankovic|Weird Al's debut album.]]
==Tracks== # [[My Bologna]] # [[School Cafeteria]]
==Trivia== *This is Al's first single. *It was originally recorded in a tiled men's bathroom across from KCPR which is a college raio station only using Weird Al's vocals and Al's accordion. *The song is talking about Bologna sausage, although referencing to Oscar Meyer's Bologna. *The original recording is on the compilation album Dr. Demento's Dementia Royale *The original recording made number 3 on Dr Demento's Funny Twenty-five. *It was re-recorded for Weird Al's [[Album:"Weird Al" Yankovic|first studio album]] *There is no official music video, although an early demo was shot showing Al lip-syncing to the song at Cal Poly San Luis Obispo in the December of 1979. It can be found as an easter egg on the DVD [[The Ultimate Video Collection]] *The capitol records version is on [[Album:Permanent Record: Al In The Box|Permanent Record.]]

