{{Infobox Album | name = Dare To Be Stupid | image = File:(AA)_Dare_To_Be_Supid.jpg‎ | imagewidth = 250px | artist = [[Albums|Studio Album]] by [["Weird Al" Yankovic]] | released = June 18, 1985 | recorded = January 1985 - March 1985 | length = 37:02 | format = Vinyl, Cassette, CD | record label = Rock 'n' Roll Records / Scotti Brothers | catalog no. = FZ 40033 (Vinyl) (first release) | genre = Comedy | producer = [[Rick Derringer]] | lead single = {{Sg|Like A Surgeon}} | previous album = {{Al|"Weird Al" Yankovic In 3-D}} | next album = {{Al|Polka Party}} }}
Dare To Be Stupid is [["Weird Al" Yankovic]]'s third studio album, including the hit single {{Sg|Like A Surgeon}}. The album was originally released on Viynl and Cassette and eventually CD. It was also re-issued on CD on the label Volcano Records. The album included 6 singles, being the record of the most singles on one Weird Al album. ==Singles== # {{Sg|This Is The Life}} # {{Sg|Like A Surgeon}} # {{Sg|I Want A New Duck}} # {{Sg|One More Minute}} # {{Sg|Hooked On Polkas}} # {{Sg|Dare To Be Stupid}}
