[[File:ABS.jpg|200px|thumb|Single Cover]]
Song: '''Achy Breaky Song'''

Running Time: '''3:23'''

Year: '''1993'''

Album: '''[[Alapalooza]], {{Al|Achy Breaky Song}}'''

Parody of: '''{{W|Achy Breaky Heart}} by {{W|Billy Ray Cyrus}}'''

Lyrics: '''[[Lyrics:Achy Breaky Song|Lyrics]]'''

Video: '''None'''

Forum: '''[http://www.weirdalforum.com/forum/index.php?showtopic=6616 Forum Discussion Page]'''

==The Song==
*"Achy Breaky Song" is "Weird Al" Yankovic's parody of "Achy Breaky Heart" by Billy Ray Cyrus. The song details a disgruntled listener's disdain for it ("Don't play that song, that achy breaky song..."), as well as several alternatives he would rather endure, rather than having to listen to it anymore. These even include physical torture such as being "tied to a chair and kicked down the stairs".

==Musicians and Bands Mentioned in the Song==
*{{W|Donny & Marie}}
*{{W|Barry Manilow}}
*{{W|New Kids on the Block}}
*{{W|Village People}}
*{{W|Vanilla Ice}}
*{{W|Bee Gees}}
*{{W|Billy Ray Cyrus}}
*{{W|Debby Boone}}
*{{W|ABBA}}
*{{W|Slim Whitman}}
*{{W|Zamfir}}
*{{W|Yoko Ono}}
*{{W|Tiffany}}

==Trivia==
* Eighteen years after this song was released (no jobs), Al parodied Billy Ray's daughter, Miley Cyrus's, "Party in the U.S.A." with "[[Party In The CIA]]." This marks the first time that Al has parodied father/daughter artists.
[[Category:Songs]]

{{Infobox Album | name = Alpocalypse | image = File:Alpocalypsescan1.jpg | imagewidth = 250px | artist = [[Albums|Studio Album]] by [["Weird Al" Yankovic]] | released = June 21, 2011 | recorded = September 2008 – April 2011 | length = CD: 45:56, DVD: 37:35 | record label = Jive / Way Moby / Volcano | catalog no. = 88697-89326-2 (CD) (first release) | genre = Comedy | producer = Al Yankovic | lead single = {{Sg|Perform This Way}} | previous album = {{Al|Straight Outta Lynwood}} | next album = {{Al|Album 14}} (Spoiler Alert!) }}
'''Alpocalypse''' is [["Weird Al" Yankovic]]'s 13th studio album. It was Al's first album in five years, being the longest length between an album getting released. The first single released was "[[Whatever You Like]]", a parody of T.I's "Whatever You Like" in 2008. 4 other of the singles were released in 2009 and Yankovic made an EP out of those 5 tracks named the [[EP:Internet Leaks|Internet Leaks EP.]] He said it was an experiment to see how he could release songs for an album.
The album was released as a CD, Digital Download and Vinyl Record, being the first album since {{Al|UHF - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack and Other Stuff}} to be released on record (although {{Al|Straight Outta Lynwood}} had a 12" EP named {{EP|Selections From Straight Outta Lynwood}}.)
==Singles== #{{Sg|Whatever You Like}} #{{Sg|Craigslist}} #{{Sg|Skipper Dan}} #{{Sg|CNR}} #{{Sg|Ringtone}} #{{Sg|Perform This Way}}
